				\begin{document}$$\beta _0$$\end{document} as a global average, with each coefficient representing a deviation from this baseline. These priors also mitigate multicollinearity inherent in one-hot encoding without a reference category. For variable selection, we use sum-to-zero regularised horseshoe (SZRHS) priors28, which combine the identifiability constraint with shrinkage to induce sparsity. Further details are provided in the Supplementary Materials.

